.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-i <str>
Use <str> to indent each level of the XML tree.
The default is two spaces.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B <file>...
XML file(s) to format.
If none are specified, the utility will read from stdin.
.RS
.RE
